WEBVTT

00:17.480 --> 00:19.400
Are you really ready for it?

00:20.960 --> 00:25.520
I would go away
from here, but I can't.

00:27.360 --> 00:30.280
When I can't be an emergency
room doctor anymore

00:30.720 --> 00:32.520
is it okay to be a
chaplain in the hospital?

00:33.840 --> 00:35.520
I am happy about the chance.

00:38.480 --> 00:39.800
The new drugs are not working?

00:43.240 --> 00:44.840
Have you thought about
an operation again?

00:45.040 --> 00:48.600
The brain pacemaker?
Yes, I have thought carefully.

00:49.360 --> 00:50.600
Especially with
regard to the risks...

00:51.640 --> 00:53.880
I could lose my
memories and my life.

00:54.240 --> 00:56.000
Or it can change
your life, Rollie.

00:57.160 --> 00:58.960
Fields says you would
be a good candidate.

00:59.080 --> 01:00.240
But maybe not much longer.

01:00.360 --> 01:01.600
Yes I know that.

01:02.200 --> 01:05.680
I think you should change
your mind because...

01:07.480 --> 01:11.120
It looks like a disaster,
an apartment fire.

01:11.240 --> 01:13.400
Look, I understand what you
were saying, Dr.  Campbell.

01:13.560 --> 01:14.920
But I've made up my mind.

01:15.320 --> 01:18.920
Fine, but there are
rules for your new job.

01:19.560 --> 01:21.560
You can give advice and comfort

01:21.680 --> 01:22.840
to those who
wish, but you can...

01:23.080 --> 01:27.160
I am not allowed to
treat patients, understood.

01:34.480 --> 01:36.240
The first emergency vehicle will
be on the ramp in two minutes.

01:36.640 --> 01:38.400
Hey guys.  30 to 40
patients come straight away.

01:38.800 --> 01:41.000
So smoke inhalation,
burns and injuries.

01:41.120 --> 01:43.440
You in the second year, what
do you do first with burn victims?

01:43.720 --> 01:46.360
-Intubate early...
-... with burned airways.

01:46.480 --> 01:47.440
Expect fluid deficit.

01:47.560 --> 01:48.640
Rollie, good to see you.

01:48.760 --> 01:49.920
Likewise, Leanne.

01:50.280 --> 01:52.720
-Dr.  Guthrie...
-No, I'm just Rollie.

01:53.320 --> 01:54.520
You're still a doctor.

01:55.000 --> 01:56.840
This way I don't
confuse the patients.

01:56.960 --> 01:58.240
I am there to support you.

01:58.920 --> 01:59.880
That pleases me.

02:00.080 --> 02:02.000
Leighton, Pineda,
Savetti, take care!

02:02.560 --> 02:04.200
Disturbed families
are coming soon.

02:04.320 --> 02:05.360
Yes, I will be there.

02:08.880 --> 02:09.840
What's up?

02:09.960 --> 02:11.920
A 55-year-old, smoke inhalation
and shortness of breath.

02:12.040 --> 02:13.200
He complains of
severe chest pain.

02:13.440 --> 02:15.200
Lola?  Lola!

02:15.680 --> 02:16.680
-His daughter.
-Lola!

02:16.800 --> 02:18.800
She lost her balance as
she helped him up the ladder.

02:18.920 --> 02:19.880
She fell two floors.

02:20.000 --> 02:21.680
-Come with you?
-No, another car.

02:21.800 --> 02:22.760
What is going on here?

02:22.880 --> 02:25.280
A 28 year old.  2nd degree
burns to chest and neck.

02:25.400 --> 02:27.040
Diffuse wheezing
after smoke inhalation.

02:27.160 --> 02:28.720
Okay, why is it fixed?

02:29.040 --> 02:30.760
Acute restlessness.
Absolutely incoherent.

02:30.880 --> 02:33.480
She must be confused
about the lack of oxygen.

02:35.200 --> 02:37.480
My daughter.  She saved me.

02:37.600 --> 02:38.680
Let's take him to
the Center Stage.

02:42.200 --> 02:45.440
It's arabic.  She's talking
about a baby.  Is there a baby

02:45.560 --> 02:47.600
There may be a baby in
one of the cars.  Check it out!

02:47.720 --> 02:50.720
Eloise, ask at
headquarters for a baby

02:50.840 --> 02:53.320
- that came unaccompanied.
-Get a translator.

02:53.760 --> 02:54.760
Center Stage?

02:55.040 --> 02:56.360
Is busy.
It has to be in the side panel.

02:56.720 --> 02:58.040
Where is he?  Where is the child?

02:58.160 --> 03:00.240
Sir, lean back in.
You have to breathe.

03:00.360 --> 03:01.320
Child?  Her child?

03:01.440 --> 03:04.280
No!  The little bastard that
it was.  He started the fire!

03:04.400 --> 03:05.680
He burned down my building!

03:08.000 --> 03:10.640
Breathe with me.
Breathe... calmly...

03:11.240 --> 03:12.280
Your wheezing is getting worse.

03:12.800 --> 03:15.920
We need ventilation and 5
units of Haldoperidol per IV.

03:16.040 --> 03:17.000
Scissors.

03:17.320 --> 03:19.840
-What do you have here?
-A 26 year old, passed out,

03:20.280 --> 03:22.760
blunt injuries on the abdomen,
defensive tension and on both sides

03:22.880 --> 03:25.040
Injuries to the lower
limbs, pulse not felt.

03:25.160 --> 03:26.360
Okay, Doppler confirmation.

03:26.480 --> 03:27.440
That's okay.

03:27.560 --> 03:28.560
Hurry up.

03:29.600 --> 03:31.320
I need to know how
my daughter is doing.

03:31.440 --> 03:34.920
Where's Lola?  My chest hurts

03:35.040 --> 03:36.240
I will give you pain medication.

03:36.360 --> 03:38.400
He has to go to cardiology,
looks like a heart attack.

03:38.520 --> 03:41.600
That is not enough.  At 1 and
2, the ST extension depression,

03:41.720 --> 03:44.000
-and the increase under aVR?
- Infarct, left main artery.

03:44.120 --> 03:45.760
He'll need a bypass.

03:45.880 --> 03:47.440
Let the OP know.
Prepare everything.

03:47.560 --> 03:50.280
No blood flow in the foot, it
needs to be directed.  Dr.  Willis?

03:50.400 --> 03:51.360
I'm on my way.

03:52.000 --> 03:53.280
Thank you.  Ready?

03:54.720 --> 03:57.520
Do you have the foot?
One two Three.

03:59.880 --> 04:01.200
Dr.  Willis!
He's having a heart attack!

04:01.880 --> 04:03.800
Go on, check the
pulse and re-shine.

04:03.920 --> 04:04.880
I start the resuscitation.

04:10.880 --> 04:13.640
Daddy  Daddy!  I love you.

04:15.120 --> 04:16.560
We have to get him
out of here right now.

04:17.800 --> 04:18.760
Dad!

04:20.560 --> 04:21.839
Daddy i love you

04:22.640 --> 04:24.520
-Daddy.
-Keep still, okay?

04:24.640 --> 04:25.720
Your ankle is not stable.

04:25.840 --> 04:29.320
Your dad had a heart attack
and is going to be operated on.

04:29.600 --> 04:30.840
We take care of him.

04:30.960 --> 04:32.560
Good blood circulation in the foot.

04:32.840 --> 04:35.200
She needs an abdominal
CT after splinting.

04:35.320 --> 04:36.280
The drugs are there.

04:36.400 --> 04:38.400
OK.
Kerlix and silver sulfadiazine.

04:38.560 --> 04:39.560
Will be done.

04:40.040 --> 04:41.440
A boy of four months.

04:41.880 --> 04:44.520
Slight burns 1st and
2nd degree, good values.

04:44.640 --> 04:47.240
See, your baby was found.
He is safe.

04:50.880 --> 04:51.880
He has to go to the neonatal unit.

04:52.000 --> 04:53.040
Let her see him, please.

04:53.160 --> 04:54.680
She can't hold him
because of the burns.

04:55.120 --> 04:56.080
You're welcome.

04:56.200 --> 04:57.320
Here you go.  Fast.

04:57.480 --> 04:58.600
OK?  Chill out.

04:59.360 --> 05:01.480
There it is, see?

05:01.680 --> 05:03.800
He's okay  I have
to treat him now.

05:07.320 --> 05:08.280
He'll be over there.

05:08.400 --> 05:09.360
Chill out.

05:10.920 --> 05:12.760
Something is not right.

05:12.880 --> 05:14.000
-She said babies.
-What?

05:14.120 --> 05:16.240
Babies.  Not baby, babies.

05:17.360 --> 05:18.800
Moment.  There are two?

05:18.920 --> 05:19.880
Are there two babies?

05:23.040 --> 05:24.120
There are two.  They are twins.

05:32.480 --> 05:35.480
Tell the driver to
turn off the alarm.

05:36.080 --> 05:37.040
Okay good.

05:37.800 --> 05:40.680
I said they are twins.
They just brought us a baby.

05:40.800 --> 05:42.360
We made some
sacrifices at St. Joe's.

05:42.480 --> 05:43.680
I called St. Joe's.

05:43.800 --> 05:45.920
Well, I'll check.  Description?

05:46.440 --> 05:48.440
About six months, female...

05:48.680 --> 05:51.600
Do I really have to
describe a baby to you?

05:51.920 --> 05:55.240
You know what?  Just bring
all of the babies here, okay?

05:55.680 --> 05:58.600
I need to see my father, please.

06:01.040 --> 06:03.960
Can anyone hear me
Is there a doctor here?

06:04.200 --> 06:05.720
-Someone who...
-What's going on here?

06:05.840 --> 06:09.120
I want to see my father,
but nobody brings me to him.

06:09.240 --> 06:10.760
Because you have two broken legs

06:11.120 --> 06:13.240
and a liver injury.
You have nowhere to go

06:13.360 --> 06:14.480
He's also still in the operating room.

06:15.680 --> 06:17.560
Do you want to be fixed

06:17.760 --> 06:18.960
You don't understand.

06:19.160 --> 06:22.440
We argued and...
I said something.

06:23.280 --> 06:24.800
Fathers and daughters
are always fighting.

06:25.520 --> 06:28.480
What I said to him must
not have been the last.

06:30.200 --> 06:31.720
I have to tell him I'm sorry.

06:32.320 --> 06:34.480
When he's out of the operating
room, I'll try to take you there.

06:34.840 --> 06:35.880
When?

06:37.080 --> 06:39.640
Hey Risa.  How about Emanuel?

06:40.160 --> 06:43.000
No you have to do that.

06:43.520 --> 06:44.760
That can't wait.

06:45.560 --> 06:47.160
You have to tell him I'm sorry.

06:49.000 --> 06:50.040
You're welcome.

06:52.720 --> 06:55.280
That's crazy.
Rollie Guthrie has the jackpot.

06:55.400 --> 06:57.040
The operation cannot be
performed on everyone.

06:58.880 --> 07:00.960
Okay, sew the fabric
away from the blockage.

07:01.240 --> 07:03.320
Next to the left
coronary artery.  All right.

07:03.640 --> 07:05.120
You told him time
is running out, right?

07:05.240 --> 07:06.880
That he won't be a
candidate forever?

07:08.200 --> 07:09.200
He knows that.

07:09.480 --> 07:10.440
This is insane.

07:10.560 --> 07:12.000
- Did you ask him why?
-I beg your pardon?

07:12.280 --> 07:13.240
Of course not.

07:13.360 --> 07:15.040
Try to ask him why he
doesn't want the surgery.

07:15.240 --> 07:16.480
Maybe he has a good reason.

07:21.640 --> 07:24.560
She says the baby was in
the back room, it's called Adira.

07:24.680 --> 07:25.800
She speaks very quickly.

07:27.960 --> 07:30.120
I understand.

07:30.800 --> 07:34.640
Not your words, but what
you're going through, okay?

07:37.520 --> 07:38.600
Dr.  Rorish.

07:43.800 --> 07:46.160
We found the baby.
It'll come in a few minutes.

07:47.240 --> 07:48.280
How is the condition?

07:50.600 --> 07:52.960
It is alive, but it
shows no reaction.

07:55.160 --> 07:56.720
Should i tell her

08:01.160 --> 08:02.480
No not yet.

08:10.000 --> 08:12.200
Are you still in pain?
We can give you more.

08:14.240 --> 08:17.160
That's him!  That's him!
He burned my house down!

08:17.280 --> 08:18.640
Sir, you have to
stay in your bed, yes?

08:18.760 --> 08:22.480
Jared!  Thank god!
Can you hear me?  Jared?

08:22.600 --> 08:25.120
This is my son.  Is he alright?
Why is he not responding?

08:25.240 --> 08:27.680
He has 2nd degree burns
on his chest and stomach.

08:27.960 --> 08:29.920
See who finally shows up.

08:30.240 --> 08:31.480
What?  Larry!

08:31.640 --> 08:34.400
Twice a week I'll
turn off your fire alarm

08:34.520 --> 08:36.000
because your child
is burning their food.

08:36.120 --> 08:37.080
He likes to cook.

08:37.200 --> 08:39.080
He has to cook.
You are never there.

08:39.520 --> 08:40.679
I blame you!

08:40.799 --> 08:44.200
Your irresponsibility burned
the whole house down!

08:44.320 --> 08:46.080
It wasn't me, dad.  I swear.

08:46.200 --> 08:47.320
Just stay down.

08:47.440 --> 08:49.120
If my son says it
wasn't him, it wasn't him.

08:49.240 --> 08:50.320
Call the police!

08:50.440 --> 08:51.400
Leave him in peace!

08:51.520 --> 08:53.080
-It's just your...
-Don't touch me.

08:53.200 --> 08:55.000
That's enough!
I said that's enough!

08:55.120 --> 08:57.640
Come on, get her out.
Go back to your bed.

08:57.760 --> 09:00.640
You left him alone.
These people are dead.

09:01.160 --> 09:02.360
This is your fault, Devon!

09:05.240 --> 09:06.600
-Dr.  Rorish.
-Forgiveness.  What do we have here?

09:06.760 --> 09:09.320
A 30 year old with minor
injuries, severe bradycardia

09:09.440 --> 09:10.800
Hypotensive from
smoke inhalation.

09:10.920 --> 09:12.840
Center Stage is full,
take her to the side area.

09:13.360 --> 09:14.400
Your son, Jack.

09:17.520 --> 09:19.760
Hi Jack.  We'll take good
care of your mom, right?

09:20.200 --> 09:21.400
Eloise will take care of you.

09:22.360 --> 09:24.720
Ok go  She needs
high-flow oxygen.

09:27.200 --> 09:28.920
Ready?  One two Three.

09:37.880 --> 09:38.880
Check your pulse, Malaya.

09:40.800 --> 09:42.040
The pulse is down to around 20.

09:42.160 --> 09:44.440
Atropine doesn't work.
Should we give her dopamine?

09:45.040 --> 09:46.680
The fire department found
this next to her in her room.

09:48.560 --> 09:49.520
Atenolol.

09:49.640 --> 09:51.200
This is a beta blocker overdose.

09:51.360 --> 09:52.760
Dopamine doesn't work,
she needs glucagon.

09:52.880 --> 09:54.800
I'm losing her pulse,
starting resuscitation.

09:58.040 --> 09:59.920
Dr.  Willis, did you
want to see me?

10:00.560 --> 10:02.280
I want to know how
Emanuel Johnson is doing.

10:02.440 --> 10:04.440
Still unconscious,
but stable.  How so?

10:04.560 --> 10:05.960
I have a message
from his daughter.

10:06.080 --> 10:07.240
When he wakes up,
will you page me?

10:08.640 --> 10:10.120
Dr.  Willis, it's about Lola.

10:11.280 --> 10:12.240
What happened?

10:12.360 --> 10:14.680
She wanted to see her dad, and
her blood pressure plummeted.

10:14.800 --> 10:15.920
We have a baby here.

10:18.160 --> 10:19.120
Is this the other twin?

10:19.440 --> 10:21.160
The paramedics just found them.
No burns.

10:21.280 --> 10:23.560
She was stuck in a
room full of smoke.

10:23.760 --> 10:26.080
The pulse is slow at
160, capillarization time.

10:26.240 --> 10:27.600
Dr.  Dixon, what do you see?

10:28.320 --> 10:31.360
Retinal hemorrhage.
And cherry skin.

10:31.600 --> 10:33.000
This is CO poisoning.

10:37.120 --> 10:38.760
-Mommy?
-Sorry, he ran away.

10:38.880 --> 10:39.840
Get him out now!

10:41.840 --> 10:42.840
The glucagon is there.

10:42.960 --> 10:43.920
It has to work.

10:50.360 --> 10:51.960
Looks like she tore
open the liver wound.

10:52.080 --> 10:53.200
We have to stop the bleeding.

10:53.400 --> 10:54.520
Your stomach is full of blood.

10:54.960 --> 10:56.160
Center Stage, go.

10:57.000 --> 10:58.640
Put them in a
hyperbaric chamber.

10:58.760 --> 10:59.880
It needs hyperbaric
oxygen to replace

11:00.000 --> 11:02.000
the carbon monoxide
in hemoglobin.

11:02.120 --> 11:03.480
-I'm going to get a senior doctor.
-No.

11:04.040 --> 11:05.480
Nobody is here except you.

11:05.680 --> 11:06.680
What?

11:06.800 --> 11:08.600
Four emergency vans
come up the ramp.

11:09.120 --> 11:11.160
-Rollie, go with me.
-I am not allowed to treat.

11:11.280 --> 11:12.920
You are in front of the chamber.
No time to discuss.

11:13.040 --> 11:14.040
She has to get in there immediately.

11:14.160 --> 11:15.480
-Come on!
-Let's go.

11:21.520 --> 11:25.800
Jesse, good.  Give
me two units, far up.

11:26.920 --> 11:27.880
All right.

11:28.680 --> 11:30.080
Systolic blood
pressure is at 64.

11:30.200 --> 11:32.360
Appears posterior, presumably
the inferior vena cava.

11:33.160 --> 11:34.320
Let's try a Pringle maneuver.

11:34.760 --> 11:36.280
That gives us time
until the operation.

11:39.200 --> 11:40.400
The bleeding subsides.

11:40.560 --> 11:41.600
The blood pressure rises.

11:41.720 --> 11:44.080
It's not over the mountain.
Let's take her to the operating room.

11:44.960 --> 11:46.360
Your oxygen levels drop rapidly.

11:46.480 --> 11:47.560
You have to intubate.

11:48.000 --> 11:49.320
Never have I ever
intubated a baby.

11:49.440 --> 11:50.640
Dr.  Dixon, listen to me.

11:51.600 --> 11:54.040
You are your only chance.
Do you understand?

11:56.200 --> 11:57.200
You can do it.

11:59.440 --> 12:02.160
The baby's relatively large
head causes the neck to flex.

12:02.280 --> 12:04.800
Put a towel under your
shoulder for a better view.

12:06.760 --> 12:07.800
Good Good.

12:08.360 --> 12:10.360
Very gently.

12:11.960 --> 12:13.120
Tell me what you see

12:16.000 --> 12:18.840
Nothing.  The vocal
cords are too far forward.

12:18.960 --> 12:22.280
Use a Miller laryngoscope
to elevate the epiglottis.

12:25.200 --> 12:26.400
Concentration, Dr.  Dixon.

12:26.560 --> 12:28.040
There is only you
and your patient.

12:33.160 --> 12:34.120
I see nothing.

12:34.520 --> 12:35.480
Fine

12:35.600 --> 12:38.200
Then lift it up and
slide the tube in.

12:41.920 --> 12:43.880
Your heart stopped!
I need help!

12:44.160 --> 12:46.480
-I can't open the door.
-The room is under pressure.

12:46.600 --> 12:48.040
Elliot, start the resuscitation.

13:05.360 --> 13:06.320
Check the pulse.

13:16.360 --> 13:17.320
Damn it.

13:18.520 --> 13:19.880
How long has she been asystolic?

13:21.320 --> 13:22.360
For 32 minutes.

13:30.920 --> 13:31.880
Explain death.

13:34.080 --> 13:35.040
No.

13:36.160 --> 13:37.320
No, I can go on.

13:37.440 --> 13:40.360
Dr.  Dixon, you
did what you could.

13:41.160 --> 13:44.360
You have to
explain death, I can't.

14:06.720 --> 14:08.400
Time of death, 11:01 p.m.

14:14.440 --> 14:15.560
Please get me out of here.

14:18.560 --> 14:19.720
That will not do.

14:22.880 --> 14:25.160
We have to decompress
the chamber first.

14:27.120 --> 14:28.120
How long?

14:30.200 --> 14:31.360
About an hour.

14:33.640 --> 14:34.880
I'm sorry son

14:37.000 --> 14:38.440
I wish I could have helped.

14:50.440 --> 14:51.560
Is that the pastor's daughter?

14:51.960 --> 14:52.920
Lola.

14:53.560 --> 14:55.120
Dr.  Pinkney and I stopped
the bleeding, but the

14:55.240 --> 14:59.240
liver is injured, and possibly
the vena cava as well.

14:59.880 --> 15:01.600
As long as the
vessels are supplied,

15:01.720 --> 15:03.040
we can save most of their liver.

15:03.160 --> 15:04.120
Yes...

15:04.240 --> 15:06.600
She wanted me to tell her
father something important.

15:07.240 --> 15:08.200
He's not awake.

15:08.320 --> 15:09.280
She's bleeding again.

15:09.680 --> 15:10.760
I'm coming.

15:11.720 --> 15:14.040
We didn't save
Emanuel to let her die.

15:14.680 --> 15:15.880
Can I please assist?

15:17.560 --> 15:18.520
See you in there.

15:25.640 --> 15:27.200
Rima, I'm so sorry.

15:28.880 --> 15:30.600
The doctors did
everything they could...

15:32.120 --> 15:33.800
... they couldn't
save your baby.

15:50.600 --> 15:51.680
I'm so sorry.

16:01.600 --> 16:03.400
How many died in the fire?

16:06.680 --> 16:07.800
You know Jared...

16:11.120 --> 16:14.000
We see really bad
things here every day.

16:14.400 --> 16:15.640
Terrible accidents.

16:16.400 --> 16:20.960
But they are accidents.

16:25.760 --> 16:27.960
I was playing with
fireworks on the roof.

16:29.360 --> 16:31.840
Just a few firecrackers.

16:32.440 --> 16:33.600
I was just playing around.

16:34.880 --> 16:39.120
One of them caught fire
and fell down a drainpipe.

16:40.840 --> 16:43.480
I was scared of what to say.
I shouldn't be up there.

16:44.280 --> 16:46.640
I didn't know anything
was happening.

16:50.920 --> 16:54.240
All of these people
are hurt because of me.

16:59.280 --> 17:00.720
You are dead because of me.

17:18.800 --> 17:20.119
How long is he in there?

17:22.319 --> 17:23.480
Thirty-seven minutes.

